{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "To achieve this, we introduce Stratified Masking based on two principles: (1) all words in our corpus have a non-zero probability of being masked, and",
    "(2) words more likely to be found in a general corpus are masked with lower probability.",
    "With these principles, each word in our corpus is assigned to one of the following three strata:",
    "Stopwords which are generally the most frequent words in a language.",
    "Utilizing NLTK's list of 179 stopwords (Bird, 2006), we apply a 0.15 masking rate to these words."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Utilizing NLTK's list of 179 stopwords (Bird, 2006), we apply a 0.15 masking rate to these words."
  ]
}